WEBVTT

00:07.133 --> 00:10.000
SAY YOU COULD PICK ANY
SUPERHERO TO BE YOUR DAD.

00:10.000 --> 00:11.300
WHO WOULD YOU CHOOSE?

00:11.300 --> 00:12.734
BATMAN, NO QUESTION.

00:12.734 --> 00:16.367
LIVE IN A COOL CAVE,
BORROW THE BATMOBILE.

00:16.367 --> 00:18.100
HE LETS ROBIN
HANG OUT WITH HIM

00:18.100 --> 00:19.500
AND PLAY
WITH ALL HIS STUFF.

00:19.500 --> 00:21.233
AND ROBIN'S NOT
EVEN HIS REAL KID.

00:21.233 --> 00:22.233
HE'S HIS WARD.

00:22.233 --> 00:24.467
HOW DO YOU GET
TO BE A WARD?

00:24.467 --> 00:25.467
BATMAN?

00:25.467 --> 00:28.367
IS HE FASTER
THAN A SPEEDING BULLET?

00:28.367 --> 00:30.000
I DON'T THINK SO.

00:30.000 --> 00:33.367
IS HE MORE POWERFUL
THAN A LOCOMOTIVE?

00:33.367 --> 00:34.400
UH-UH.

00:35.834 --> 00:37.400
I'D WANT SUPERMAN.

00:37.400 --> 00:38.567
SEES THROUGH WALLS.

00:38.567 --> 00:40.934
YOU'D NEVER GET AWAY
WITH ANYTHING.

00:40.934 --> 00:45.100
BECAUSE I'D MAKE SOMEBODY
A VERY COOL WARD.

00:45.100 --> 00:48.000
I'D LIKE TO HAVE
SUPERMAN FOR A DAD.

00:48.000 --> 00:49.400
HEY, THERE'S MINKUS.

00:54.100 --> 00:55.467
OW.

00:55.467 --> 00:58.967
WHOA! THE 2000-X
HYDRO-SATURATOR.

00:58.967 --> 01:00.567
CAREFUL. IF FEENY
SEES THIS BABY

01:00.567 --> 01:02.033
ON SCHOOL GROUNDS,
HE'LL SHAG IT,

01:02.033 --> 01:04.000
AND I'LL HAVE TO SIT
OUT THE WATER WAR.

01:04.000 --> 01:08.200
GENTLEMEN, MEET
THE HYDRO-SAT 3000-Z.

01:08.200 --> 01:10.900
BLOW YOUR HEAD CLEAN OFF.

01:10.900 --> 01:12.700
THE 3000?

01:12.700 --> 01:14.233
THAT'S NOT EVEN
SUPPOSED TO COME OUT

01:14.233 --> 01:15.300
TILL CHRISTMAS.

01:15.300 --> 01:16.467
I KNOW A GUY.

01:20.000 --> 01:21.900
YOU REALLY
SHOULDN'T DO THAT.

01:21.900 --> 01:23.934
WHAT, ARE YOU GOING TO MELT?

01:23.934 --> 01:24.900
NO.

01:30.700 --> 01:32.567
I'M GOING TO RETALIATE.

01:36.600 --> 01:37.734
GO AHEAD...

01:37.734 --> 01:40.600
MAKE ME WET.

01:46.500 --> 01:49.767
WISE CHOICE.

01:49.767 --> 01:52.200
AH, WHO NEEDS
ONE OF THOSE?

01:52.200 --> 01:53.600
FOR YOUR INFORMATION,

01:53.600 --> 01:55.567
A WELL-PLACED
WATER BALLOON

01:55.567 --> 01:57.600
CAN GIVE YOU
JUST AS MUCH SPLASH

01:57.600 --> 01:58.767
FOR YOUR CASH.

01:58.767 --> 02:00.367
LIKE EVERYONE'S
GONNA HAVE

02:00.367 --> 02:01.834
A HUMONGOUS
WATER GUN.

02:07.100 --> 02:08.600
HOW ARE YOU?

02:08.600 --> 02:11.033
AAH! AAH!
STOP!

02:11.033 --> 02:13.233
I'LL GET ONE!
I PROMISE!

02:13.233 --> 02:14.367
OH, MY G--

02:14.367 --> 02:16.033
I'LL GET ONE!
STOP!

02:16.033 --> 02:17.500
I PROMISE!

02:25.967 --> 02:28.467
MR. MATTHEWS...

02:28.467 --> 02:31.767
THE DRINKING FOUNTAIN
IS NOT A TOY.

02:43.000 --> 02:45.600
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

03:45.767 --> 03:47.300
HI, HON.
WHAT'S HORRIBLE?

03:47.300 --> 03:48.834
HMM. THE PLUMBING
IN THE BOYS' BATHROOM

03:48.834 --> 03:50.233
IS LEAKING AGAIN.

03:50.233 --> 03:51.734
I'M ON IT.

03:51.734 --> 03:53.734
YOU ARE AN AMAZING GUY.

03:53.734 --> 03:55.467
HEY, DAD, HOW ABOUT
SOME QUALITY TIME

03:55.467 --> 03:56.667
WITH YOUR SON?

03:56.667 --> 03:58.467
I CAN'T. I'M SPENDING
SOME QUALITY TIME

03:58.467 --> 04:00.100
WITH YOUR TOILET.

04:00.100 --> 04:02.567
BUT YOU JUST GOT HOME
FROM WORK.

04:02.567 --> 04:05.600
HI, MOM. WOW,
DINNER SMELLS TERRIFIC,

04:05.600 --> 04:07.567
AND THAT THING YOU'RE WEARING
IS REALLY LOVELY.

04:09.400 --> 04:11.100
WHAT IS THAT,
A DRESS?

04:11.100 --> 04:14.500
OH, CORY, WHAT A LOVELY
AND SINCERE COMPLIMENT,

04:14.500 --> 04:16.734
AND I JUST KNOW THAT
YOU WOULDN'T SPOIL IT

04:16.734 --> 04:18.233
BY ASKING ME
FOR SOMETHING.

04:18.233 --> 04:20.600
EERIE HOW SHE ALWAYS
KNOWS, HUH?

04:20.600 --> 04:23.100
WHAT, DO ALL WOMEN
HAVE ANTENNAS

04:23.100 --> 04:25.400
HIDDEN SOMEWHERE
ON THEIR BODIES?

04:25.400 --> 04:29.100
I DON'T KNOW. NONE OF THEM
WILL LET ME LOOK.

04:29.100 --> 04:31.200
LOOK. OK, LOOK,
SAY YOU'RE IN THE KITCHEN

04:31.200 --> 04:33.800
AND THE LIVING ROOM
BURST INTO FLAMES.

04:33.800 --> 04:35.133
WHY?

04:35.133 --> 04:37.200
I DON'T KNOW.
MAYBE LIGHTNING HIT IT.

04:37.200 --> 04:38.467
WHY?

04:38.467 --> 04:39.667
BECAUSE IT WAS ATTRACTED

04:39.667 --> 04:41.700
BY THE METAL PLATE
IN YOUR HEAD.

04:41.700 --> 04:44.867
AND YOU CAN'T ESCAPE
'CAUSE YOUR LEGS ARE BROKEN.

04:44.867 --> 04:47.033
WHAT WILL YOU DO?

04:47.033 --> 04:49.000
WHY ARE HER LEGS BROKEN?

04:49.000 --> 04:51.000
BECAUSE SHE TRIPPED
OVER YOUR DEAD BODY.

04:53.967 --> 04:56.700
CORY, SPIT IT OUT.
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

04:56.700 --> 04:57.900
JUST A WATER GUN.
YOU KNOW,

04:57.900 --> 05:00.400
SO YOU CAN PUT OUT
THAT FIRE IN THE LIVING ROOM.

05:00.400 --> 05:02.100
FINE. I'LL BUY
YOUA WATER GUN.

05:02.100 --> 05:03.600
COOL.
HERE'S THE BROCHURE.

05:03.600 --> 05:05.367
COLOR CHART'S
ON THE BACK.

05:05.367 --> 05:07.200
HOW MUCH DO
THESE THINGS COST?

05:07.200 --> 05:08.867
HOW CAN YOU PUT A PRICE

05:08.867 --> 05:11.400
ON THE SAFETY
OF YOUR FAMILY?

05:11.400 --> 05:12.700
$50?

05:12.700 --> 05:15.600
$49.95...PLUS TAX,
BUT--

05:15.600 --> 05:18.000
I'LL TAKE MY CHANCES
WITH THE LIGHTNING.

05:18.000 --> 05:19.233
COME ON, MOM.

05:19.233 --> 05:23.033
YOU AND DAD BLOW THAT MUCH
MONEY ON FOOD EVERY WEEK.

05:23.033 --> 05:25.300
YOUR BATHROOM SINK
DOESN'T LEAK NOW.

05:25.300 --> 05:28.200
WOW, DAD. YOU FIXED IT
ALL BY YOURSELF?

05:28.200 --> 05:29.367
YEAH, AND YOUR TOILET

05:29.367 --> 05:32.033
DOESN'T DO THAT GEYSER
THING ANYMORE, EITHER.

05:32.033 --> 05:34.133
YOU NEVER CEASE
TO AMAZE ME.

05:34.133 --> 05:36.133
HOW MUCH DO YOU FIGURE
YOU SAVED ON A PLUMBER?

05:36.133 --> 05:39.400
WHAT'S HE WANT THIS TIME?

05:39.400 --> 05:41.667
A $50 SQUIRT GUN.

05:41.667 --> 05:43.000
A $50 SQUIRT GUN?

05:43.000 --> 05:45.233
NO, REALLY,
WHAT'S HE WANT?

05:45.233 --> 05:47.734
DAD, WE'RE NOT TALKING
AN ORDINARY SQUIRT GUN.

05:47.734 --> 05:51.000
WE'RE TALKING
THE HYDRO-SAT 3000-Z.

05:51.000 --> 05:53.967
IT'S THE BIG BOY
ON THE BLOCK.

05:53.967 --> 05:55.100
THAT'S NICE, COR.

05:55.100 --> 05:58.367
PRETTY STEEP, THOUGH.
MAYBE FOR CHRISTMAS.

05:58.367 --> 06:00.700
HEY, GREAT,
A WATER GUN IN DECEMBER.

06:00.700 --> 06:03.500
I'LL BE THE LITTLE BOY
SPREADING PNEUMONIA.

06:07.000 --> 06:09.100
IF THEY CAN'T
AFFORD TO BUY TOYS

06:09.100 --> 06:10.233
FOR 3 CHILDREN,

06:10.233 --> 06:12.300
WHY DID THEY HAVE
3 CHILDREN?

06:12.300 --> 06:13.300
LEAVE ME ALONE.

06:13.300 --> 06:15.734
I'M TRYING TO PUT HEATHER
IN MY WATCH.

06:15.734 --> 06:16.834
WHAT?

06:16.834 --> 06:19.500
I CAN'T GET IT OUT
OF VIDEO BASEBALL MODE.

06:19.500 --> 06:22.000
[BEEPS BASEBALL CHARGE]

06:22.000 --> 06:24.367
HEY, HOW'D YOU
GET MOM AND DAD

06:24.367 --> 06:25.567
TO BUY THAT FOR YOU?

06:25.567 --> 06:26.834
I BOUGHT IT FOR ME.

06:26.834 --> 06:28.867
I CASHED
MY FIRST WEEK'S PAYCHECK,

06:28.867 --> 06:29.934
WENT DOWN TO THE MALL.

06:29.934 --> 06:32.567
WELCOME TO THE WONDERFUL
WORLD OF STUFF.

06:32.567 --> 06:35.133
MOM AND DAD JUST
LET YOU BUY THAT?

06:35.133 --> 06:36.233
YEAH, THEY SAID
IT'S MY MONEY.

06:36.233 --> 06:37.600
I CAN BUY
ANYTHING I WANT,

06:37.600 --> 06:40.767
EXCEPT THAT
<i>BUNS OF STEEL </i>VIDEO.

06:40.767 --> 06:42.600
ERIC, YOU KNOW,
I'M THINKING.

06:42.600 --> 06:44.800
NOW THAT YOU'RE RAKING
IN THE BIG BUCKS,

06:44.800 --> 06:46.233
MAYBE YOU'D LIKE
TO CONSIDER

06:46.233 --> 06:49.133
THIS EXCITING
INVESTMENT OPPORTUNITY.

06:49.133 --> 06:51.200
CALL MY BROKER--

06:51.200 --> 06:52.900
SHEARSON,
LEAVE ME ALONE.

06:54.767 --> 06:58.767
BIG MAN--DOESN'T EVEN
KNOW WHAT TIME IT IS.

06:58.767 --> 07:00.200
I DO SO.

07:00.200 --> 07:02.667
IT IS...12:00.

07:02.667 --> 07:05.667
12:00, 12:00.

07:05.667 --> 07:07.967
[BEEPS BASEBALL CHARGE]

07:14.400 --> 07:16.100
SEE? I'M NOT GETTING

07:16.100 --> 07:17.967
ANY KIND
OF PRESSURE HERE.

07:17.967 --> 07:20.000
YOU HAD TO HAVE A HOUSE.

07:20.000 --> 07:22.100
REMEMBER THE APARTMENT?

07:22.100 --> 07:24.000
REMEMBER
BEFORE THE CHILDREN?

07:24.000 --> 07:25.767
BEFORE WE WERE MARRIED?

07:25.767 --> 07:27.200
BEFORE WE KNEW EACH OTHER?

07:27.200 --> 07:29.600
REMEMBER HOW HAPPY
WE WERE?

07:32.200 --> 07:33.467
OOH! OW!

07:33.467 --> 07:36.967
YOU REMEMBER WHEN YOU
KNEW WHEN I WAS KIDDING?

07:38.133 --> 07:39.767
DAD, YOU BUSY?

07:39.767 --> 07:43.500
NO. I'M JUST RELAXING
WITH MY WRENCH.

07:43.500 --> 07:45.767
I WANT A JOB
AT THE MARKET.

07:45.767 --> 07:47.600
YOU'RE TOO YOUNG FOR
A JOB AT THE MARKET.

07:47.600 --> 07:50.467
YOU LET ERIC
BE A BOX BOY.

07:50.467 --> 07:51.700
SON, YOU'RE YOUNG.

07:51.700 --> 07:53.500
ENJOY IT.
IT DOESN'T LAST LONG.

07:53.500 --> 07:56.100
WELL, I COULD WORK
AFTER SCHOOL.

07:56.100 --> 07:58.600
CORY, I DON'T HAVE
ANY OPENINGS.

07:58.600 --> 08:01.400
WELL, YOU'RE THE MANAGER.
FIRE SOMEBODY.

08:03.233 --> 08:05.834
FIRE ERIC!

08:05.834 --> 08:09.567
WHY DON'T I FIRE MYSELF
AND MAKE YOU MANAGER?

08:09.567 --> 08:11.934
COOL. WHAT'S IT PAY?

08:11.934 --> 08:15.000
NOT ENOUGH TO KEEP ME
OUT FROM UNDER THE SINK,

08:15.000 --> 08:18.033
OR THE CAR OR
THE MORTGAGE PAYMENTS.

08:18.033 --> 08:21.600
DAD,
NOBODY LIKES A WHINER.

08:21.600 --> 08:23.600
NOW, I NEED A JOB.

08:23.600 --> 08:25.400
YOU NEED TO BE A KID.

08:25.400 --> 08:27.400
I DON'T
WANT TO BE A KID.

08:27.400 --> 08:29.233
THAT'S TOO BAD,
BECAUSE ONCE IT'S GONE,

08:29.233 --> 08:30.367
YOU CAN NEVER
GET IT BACK.

08:30.367 --> 08:33.000
I WANT TO BE ABLE
TO AFFORD STUFF!

08:33.000 --> 08:34.600
SO DO I!

08:37.900 --> 08:40.834
HEY, MR. FEENY.
WHATCHA DOIN'?

08:42.367 --> 08:44.767
IMMERSING MYSELF
IN THE TRANQUILITY

08:44.767 --> 08:46.100
OF MY ROSE GARDEN

08:46.100 --> 08:47.400
IN THE VAIN ATTEMPT

08:47.400 --> 08:49.400
TO OFFSET
MY EVENING AHEAD--

08:49.400 --> 08:53.233
DRUDGING THROUGH 2 DOZEN
SIXTH-GRADE ESSAYS

08:53.233 --> 08:56.500
ON EDGAR ALLAN POE'S
<i>THE RAVEN. </i>

08:56.500 --> 08:58.300
I THINK YOU'LL LIKE
MY PAPER.

08:58.300 --> 08:59.100
OH?

08:59.100 --> 09:00.100
WHAT A MAJOR FREAKOID

09:00.100 --> 09:02.200
THAT ED POE
MUST HAVE BEEN, HUH?

09:04.700 --> 09:07.834
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
HOW MAJOR A FREAKOID.

09:07.834 --> 09:10.800
SO, ARE YOU CUTTING
YOUR FLOWERS?

09:10.800 --> 09:12.100
I AM PRUNING

09:12.100 --> 09:15.000
MY PRIZED <i>EGLANTERIA </i>
<i>FLORIBUNDAS-- </i>

09:15.000 --> 09:17.100
A FRAGILE HYBRID

09:17.100 --> 09:19.400
THAT I HAVE
METICULOUSLY CULTIVATED

09:19.400 --> 09:21.467
OVER THE PAST
FEW SEASONS.

09:21.467 --> 09:23.400
WELL, FOR A SMALL FEE,

09:23.400 --> 09:25.367
I CAN HACK OFF THE REST
OF THAT DEAD STUFF.

09:28.133 --> 09:30.600
YOU STAY AWAY
FROM MY ROSES!

09:31.800 --> 09:33.667
UH, YOU KNOW, MR. FEENY,
I WAS THINKING.

09:33.667 --> 09:34.734
AUTUMN'S HERE,

09:34.734 --> 09:37.400
AND WINTER'S
JUST AROUND THE CORNER.

09:37.400 --> 09:39.967
THAT'S TYPICALLY
THE PATTERN.

09:39.967 --> 09:42.200
AND IF YOU GIVE ME
50 BUCKS NOW,

09:42.200 --> 09:44.734
I'LL SHOVEL YOUR SNOW
ALL WINTER.

09:44.734 --> 09:46.934
PAYMENT IN ADVANCE?

09:46.934 --> 09:49.400
FOR A TASK
LINKED TO FACTORS

09:49.400 --> 09:51.300
AS UNPREDICTABLE
AS THE WEATHER?

09:51.300 --> 09:52.667
HARDLY SEEMS FAIR.

09:52.667 --> 09:54.600
COME ON, MR. FEENY,
HAVE SOME PITY.

09:54.600 --> 09:57.900
I'VE BEEN OUT OF WORK
FOR 11 YEARS.

09:59.700 --> 10:02.667
WELL,
I DO HAVE SOME SHUTTERS

10:02.667 --> 10:04.600
THAT ARE IN DIRE NEED
OF PAINT.

10:04.600 --> 10:06.600
COOL. WHAT'S IT PAY?

10:06.600 --> 10:10.233
WELL, I COULD GO
AS HIGH AS, OH, 5.

10:10.233 --> 10:12.834
DOLLARS? GET A PULSE!

10:12.834 --> 10:15.800
5 BUCKS TO PAINT
ALL THOSE?

10:15.800 --> 10:19.000
$5 APIECE,
MR. MATTHEWS.

10:19.000 --> 10:21.734
THAT'S 5 TIMES
2 SHUTTERS

10:21.734 --> 10:24.000
TIMES 8 WINDOWS.

10:24.000 --> 10:28.300
5 TIMES 2...

10:28.300 --> 10:30.100
TIMES 8.

10:30.100 --> 10:32.500
WHAT'S THAT,
LIKE, 58 BUCKS?

10:36.300 --> 10:38.500
$58 IT IS.

10:41.934 --> 10:45.000
YOU ARE WORTH EVERY
INCH OF THAT C-PLUS

10:45.000 --> 10:47.000
I GAVE YOU IN MATH.

10:47.000 --> 10:48.500
THANKS, MR. FEENY.

10:48.500 --> 10:50.400
YOU WON'T REGRET IT.

10:50.400 --> 10:52.700
OH, I EXPECT I SHALL.

11:05.767 --> 11:08.033
WELL, MR. MATTHEWS,
I MUST CONFESS,

11:08.033 --> 11:09.400
I'M PLEASANTLY
SURPRISED.

11:09.400 --> 11:12.200
YOUR FIRST FORAY
INTO THE WORK FORCE

11:12.200 --> 11:13.467
IS A ROUSING
SUCCESS.

11:13.467 --> 11:17.033
YOU COMPLETED YOUR
TASKAHEAD OF SCHEDULE

11:17.033 --> 11:18.767
AND WITH A
MODICUM OF SKILL.

11:18.767 --> 11:21.000
COOL. DOES THAT MEAN
YOU'RE GIVING ME A BONUS?

11:21.000 --> 11:22.567
GET A PULSE.

11:25.500 --> 11:26.800
GOOD MORNING, ALAN.

11:26.800 --> 11:29.200
GEORGE.
KID DID OK, HUH?

11:29.200 --> 11:31.567
OH, YES.
HE ACQUITTED HIMSELF

11:31.567 --> 11:34.233
LIKE A YOUNG
EARL SCHEIB.

11:34.233 --> 11:36.100
3 COATS,
LIKE YOU SAID,

11:36.100 --> 11:38.400
AND THEY DON'T EVEN
STICK OR ANYTHING.

11:38.400 --> 11:41.467
SEE, DAD, THIS WORK STUFF
IS A PIECE OF CAKE.

11:41.467 --> 11:42.600
NOTHING TO IT.

11:42.600 --> 11:45.233
I MAY JUST START UP
MY OWN BUSINESS.

11:53.033 --> 11:54.734
YEAH? WELL,
DON'T START PRINTING UP

11:54.734 --> 11:56.500
THOSE BUSINESS CARDS
JUST YET.

11:56.500 --> 11:58.300
HMM.

11:58.300 --> 12:00.300
DOESN'T EVEN STICK.

12:00.300 --> 12:01.700
REMARKABLE.

12:05.000 --> 12:06.200
WELL, GOT TO GO.

12:06.200 --> 12:08.600
WATER WAR'S STARTING,
STARTING REAL SOON.

12:08.600 --> 12:09.900
GOTTA GO. SEE YA.

12:13.867 --> 12:16.000
I'M GONNA BE LATE,
AREN'T I?

12:25.000 --> 12:26.567
YOU KNOW HOW YOU'VE
BEEN TALKING ABOUT

12:26.567 --> 12:28.100
MAYBE REDOING
THE BACKYARD.

12:28.100 --> 12:30.233
YEAH, BUT NOW
THAT I LOOK AT IT,

12:30.233 --> 12:31.400
I DON'T THINK I WANT

12:31.400 --> 12:33.734
TO GO WITH
THIS ZEBRA MOTIF.

12:33.734 --> 12:35.000
WELL, NOBODY TOLD ME

12:35.000 --> 12:37.400
THE PAINT WAS GONNA
GO THROUGH THE SHUTTERS.

12:37.400 --> 12:39.100
CORY, WHEN YOU
OPEN THE SHUTTERS

12:39.100 --> 12:40.133
IN YOUR BEDROOM,

12:40.133 --> 12:41.767
DOES THE SUNLIGHT
GO THROUGH?

12:41.767 --> 12:43.700
WELL, YOU GOT ME.

12:43.700 --> 12:45.100
I'M AN IDIOT.

12:45.100 --> 12:47.934
NO, YOU'RE NOT AN IDIOT.
YOU'RE A KID.

12:47.934 --> 12:50.300
I'M A KIDIOT.

12:55.200 --> 12:56.767
WATER WAR TIME, CORY.

12:56.767 --> 12:58.934
WAR!

13:00.900 --> 13:03.133
WAR BRINGS OUT
THE BEAST IN MINKUS.

13:03.133 --> 13:06.600
YOU KIDS
AND YOUR WATER WARS.

13:06.600 --> 13:08.000
I'D LOVE
TO JOIN YOU,

13:08.000 --> 13:10.100
BUT I'M HAVING WAY
TOO MUCH FUN HERE.

13:10.100 --> 13:12.700
YOU'RE BAILING
ON THE WATER WAR?

13:12.700 --> 13:13.967
TO PAINT A FENCE?

13:13.967 --> 13:17.133
YOU SAY PAINT A FENCE.
I SAY PARTY.

13:18.867 --> 13:20.834
AND, BY THE WAY,
EVEN IF YOU WANTED TO,

13:20.834 --> 13:23.367
I WOULDN'T CUT YOU IN
ON THIS ACTION.

13:23.367 --> 13:25.834
WHY NOT? I THOUGHT
WE WERE FRIENDS.

13:25.834 --> 13:27.800
YEAH, HOW COME
YOU'RE CUTTING US OUT?

13:27.800 --> 13:31.500
PEOPLE, PEOPLE,
AM I THE ONLY ONE

13:31.500 --> 13:33.800
WHO READ THE SUMMER
READING LIST?

13:34.900 --> 13:36.500
<i>TOM SAWYER? </i>

13:38.400 --> 13:41.700
HE'S SUCKING YOU IN
TO DO THE WORK FOR HIM.

13:41.700 --> 13:44.033
GUYS, WHO ARE YOU
GONNA LISTEN TO,

13:44.033 --> 13:45.567
ME OR THE BANANA?

13:48.133 --> 13:49.567
WELL, LET'S SEE.

13:49.567 --> 13:52.834
THE BANANA SAYS PLAY.
YOU SAY WORK.

13:52.834 --> 13:55.934
WE'RE GONNA HANG
WITH THE BIG YELLOW GUY.

13:55.934 --> 13:58.200
OK, LOOK,
I GOT 7 BUCKS LEFT

13:58.200 --> 14:00.200
AFTER BUYING
MY HYDRO-SAT,

14:00.200 --> 14:01.100
AND IT'S YOURS

14:01.100 --> 14:02.867
IF YOU HELP ME
PAINT THE FENCE.

14:02.867 --> 14:04.400
I SAY WE HOLD OUT
FOR LUNCH,

14:04.400 --> 14:07.600
AND THAT'S MR. BANANA
TO YOU, BUD.

14:10.300 --> 14:12.500
ONE BUNNY EAR

14:12.500 --> 14:17.300
GOES AROUND
THE OTHER BUNNY EAR.

14:17.300 --> 14:19.100
WILL YOU JUST
TIE THE BOW?

14:19.100 --> 14:21.600
I'M LATE FOR THE MARKET.
DAD'S GOING TO KILL ME!

14:21.600 --> 14:24.934
I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO TIE A BOW.

14:24.934 --> 14:27.200
SO, WHY DID YOU
TELL ME YOU DID?

14:27.200 --> 14:29.600
'CAUSE I'M
SELF-CONFIDENT.

14:31.133 --> 14:33.500
[SIGHS]
NOW THEY WANT DESSERT!

14:33.500 --> 14:34.800
HOW'S WORK GOING,
MAN?

14:34.800 --> 14:36.934
WORK. I LOVE WORK.

14:36.934 --> 14:39.367
PAINT THE SHUTTERS,
PAINT THE FENCE.

14:39.367 --> 14:40.867
YOU WANT PAPER
OR YOU WANT PLASTIC?

14:40.867 --> 14:42.200
DON'T DRIP THE PAINT
ON THE ROSES.

14:42.200 --> 14:43.734
DON'T PUT THE CANS
ON THE PRODUCE.

14:43.734 --> 14:46.867
I'M WITH YOU, MAN.
I HATE BEING AN ADULT.

14:48.300 --> 14:50.000
CAN I HAVE
AN ICE CREAM?

14:50.000 --> 14:52.300
ANOTHER MOUTH
TO FEED.

14:56.834 --> 14:58.567
WHAT FLAVOR
DID YOU BRING US?

14:58.567 --> 14:59.734
VANILLA.
THEY'RE VANILLA

14:59.734 --> 15:01.300
WITH CHOCOLATE
ON THE OUTSIDE,

15:01.300 --> 15:04.934
JUST LIKE THEY'VE BEEN
FOR 1,000 YEARS!

15:04.934 --> 15:07.900
I'D REALLY PREFER
A HEATH BAR CRUNCH.

15:07.900 --> 15:09.500
YOU DO?

15:11.300 --> 15:12.667
HERE YOU ARE, MINKUS.

15:12.667 --> 15:16.100
CRUNCH ON THIS.

15:16.100 --> 15:17.200
IS IT JUST ME,

15:17.200 --> 15:18.967
OR IS HE
COPPING AN ATTITUDE?

15:18.967 --> 15:21.500
I'M BEGINNING TO FEEL
UNWELCOME HERE.

15:21.500 --> 15:23.200
WATER WAR?
WATER WAR.

15:23.200 --> 15:25.734
HEY, COME ON, COME ON!
I PAID YOU.

15:25.734 --> 15:27.000
I BROUGHT YOU SANDWICHES.

15:27.000 --> 15:28.500
I BROUGHT YOU ICE CREAM.

15:28.500 --> 15:29.400
YEAH, SO?

15:29.400 --> 15:31.000
SO I'M GONNA
SUE YOU!

15:31.000 --> 15:34.200
FINE. HAVE YOUR LAWYER
CALL MY MOM.

15:34.200 --> 15:36.467
FINE. YOU WANT
SOMETHING DONE,

15:36.467 --> 15:37.734
YOU DO IT YOURSELF.

15:37.734 --> 15:40.967
I DON'T NEED THEM.
I DON'T NEED ANYBODY.

15:40.967 --> 15:42.367
STUPID WATER WAR.

15:42.367 --> 15:44.967
WATER WARS ARE FOR KIDS.

15:44.967 --> 15:46.033
MR. MATTHEWS--

15:46.033 --> 15:49.900
I SOLD YOU MY CHILDHOOD
FOR 58 BUCKS!

15:49.900 --> 15:52.367
A PAINT DRIP,
MR. MATTHEWS,

15:52.367 --> 15:54.300
AN ACRYLIC DRIBBLE
HAS APPEARED

15:54.300 --> 15:55.900
ON MY SIDE
OF THE FENCE.

15:55.900 --> 15:57.767
I LIKE IT.

15:57.767 --> 16:00.600
I DON'T.
I WANT IT REMOVED.

16:00.600 --> 16:02.033
YOU DO?

16:04.000 --> 16:06.300
YES. EITHER THAT,
OR PERHAPS

16:06.300 --> 16:08.900
YOU'D CARE TO PAINT
THE REST OF MY SIDE

16:08.900 --> 16:10.800
TO MATCH
THE OFFENDING SPOT.

16:16.600 --> 16:18.667
OH, COME NOW,
MR. MATTHEWS.

16:18.667 --> 16:20.600
I'VE HARDLY
ASKED YOU TO DESCEND

16:20.600 --> 16:22.700
INTO THE STYGIAN
COAL SHAFTS

16:22.700 --> 16:23.767
OF WEST VIRGINIA

16:23.767 --> 16:26.133
WITH A PICKAX
AND A FLASHLIGHT.

16:26.133 --> 16:29.500
WHAT'S SOMETHING
LIKE THAT PAY?

16:31.100 --> 16:33.200
WHAT DID YOU DO
TO MY KID, GEORGE?

16:33.200 --> 16:36.667
OVERWORK,
STRESS-RELATED INJURY.

16:36.667 --> 16:38.567
YOU KNOW, ALAN,
WHEN I WAS A BOY

16:38.567 --> 16:41.900
MY FATHER HAD A STRONG
PURITANICAL BELIEF

16:41.900 --> 16:43.567
IN THE WORK ETHIC.

16:43.567 --> 16:47.200
HE USED TO WORK ME
FROM SUNUP TO SUNDOWN...

16:49.100 --> 16:50.900
AND LOOK HOW
I TURNED OUT.

16:52.300 --> 16:53.400
[DOOR SHUTS]

16:53.400 --> 16:55.367
I DON'T WANT YOU
WORKING ANYMORE.

16:57.734 --> 17:00.467
SHUTTER MARKS STILL
SHOWED AFTER ONE COAT.

17:00.467 --> 17:01.600
HAD TO BORROW FROM MOM

17:01.600 --> 17:04.400
TO BUY MORE PAINT
FOR SECOND COAT.

17:04.400 --> 17:05.233
I WORKED 2 DAYS,

17:05.233 --> 17:07.467
PAINTED 16 SHUTTERS
AND A FENCE.

17:07.467 --> 17:09.900
KNOW HOW MUCH
MONEY I MADE?

17:09.900 --> 17:12.300
I OWE 8 BUCKS.

17:12.300 --> 17:14.667
WELCOME TO ADULTHOOD.

17:14.667 --> 17:15.967
AT LEAST
YOU CAME OUT OF IT

17:15.967 --> 17:17.734
WITH THIS WATER GUN
YOU WANTED.

17:17.734 --> 17:18.800
YEAH. YOU LIKE IT?

17:18.800 --> 17:21.600
SO THIS IS THE BIG BOY
ON THE BLOCK, HUH?

17:21.600 --> 17:22.834
VERY SLICK.

17:22.834 --> 17:25.133
TOO BAD I CAN'T GO TO
THE WATER WAR TO USE IT.

17:25.133 --> 17:28.033
YOU CAN IF YOU RUN.

17:28.033 --> 17:30.300
ISN'T IT
MY RESPONSIBILITY

17:30.300 --> 17:31.667
TO FINISH PAINTING
THE FENCE?

17:31.667 --> 17:34.834
I THINK YOUR
FIRST RESPONSIBILITY

17:34.834 --> 17:38.233
IS TO STAY 11 YEARS OLD
AS LONG AS YOU CAN.

17:40.467 --> 17:42.300
HOO HOO, COOL.

17:44.500 --> 17:45.500
GO ON.

17:53.467 --> 17:55.467
AHH! WHEW!

17:55.467 --> 17:57.934
THE WATER WAR
TO END ALL WATER WARS.

17:57.934 --> 18:01.233
BOTH SIDES
ARE CLAIMING VICTORY.

18:02.800 --> 18:06.100
I'D KILL YOU,
BUT I CAN'T MOVE.

18:06.100 --> 18:09.567
BAGGING GROCERIES...
CHASING CARTS...

18:09.567 --> 18:11.400
PRICE CHECKS...

18:11.400 --> 18:14.300
SPILL ON AISLE 7!

18:14.300 --> 18:16.867
OH!
IT'S A NIGHTMARE.

18:16.867 --> 18:18.834
I ONLY WORKED
HALF A SHIFT TODAY.

18:18.834 --> 18:21.233
I DON'T KNOW
HOW HE DOES IT.

18:21.233 --> 18:22.600
WHO?

18:22.600 --> 18:23.834
DAD.

18:23.834 --> 18:26.900
12-HOUR DAYS...
NEVER SITS...

18:26.900 --> 18:29.133
EATS HIS LUNCH
STANDING UP,

18:29.133 --> 18:30.600
NEVER TAKES A BREAK.

18:30.600 --> 18:32.867
IT'S LIKE
HE'S NOT HUMAN.

18:32.867 --> 18:33.967
IT'S LIKE HE'S--

18:33.967 --> 18:35.700
IT'S LIKE
HE'S SUPERMAN.

18:35.700 --> 18:37.133
HUH?

18:37.133 --> 18:39.700
SUPERMAN'S MY DAD.

18:48.767 --> 18:51.100
I KNOW YOU FINISHED PAINTING
THE FENCE FOR ME TODAY, DAD.

18:51.100 --> 18:52.700
THAT'S ALL RIGHT, CORY.

18:52.700 --> 18:56.233
NO. IT'S NOT
ALL RIGHT.

18:56.233 --> 18:58.567
YOU WORK ALL DAY,
THEN YOU COME HOME

18:58.567 --> 19:02.400
AND WORK SOME MORE,
AND THEN YOU DO MY WORK.

19:02.400 --> 19:05.200
YOU'RE HOGGING
ALL THE WORK.

19:05.200 --> 19:08.000
AND I'M CALLING YOU OUT.

19:08.000 --> 19:09.567
HUH?

19:12.300 --> 19:14.500
I'M CALLING YOU OUT.

19:14.500 --> 19:15.667
CORY--
DRAW.

19:15.667 --> 19:17.000
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

19:17.000 --> 19:18.700
[ALL SHOUT]

19:18.700 --> 19:20.500
WHAT DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE DOING?

19:20.500 --> 19:22.133
I THINK
I'M BEING A KID, MA!

19:22.133 --> 19:24.500
I THINK I'M LIVING UP
TO MY RESPONSIBILITY

19:24.500 --> 19:26.100
OF BEING 11 YEARS OLD.

19:26.100 --> 19:28.200
HEY, HEY! NO,
LISTEN, I'M SERIOUS!

19:28.200 --> 19:29.467
I'VE HAD
A VERY ROUGH DAY.

19:29.467 --> 19:31.000
WE DO NOT SHOOT
WATER PISTOLS

19:31.000 --> 19:32.200
AT THE DINNER TABLE.

19:32.200 --> 19:34.700
YOU WOULD
IF YOU HAD ONE.

19:34.700 --> 19:35.934
WHAT?

19:35.934 --> 19:38.500
GO AHEAD. MAYBE THERE'S
A LITTLE SURPRISE

19:38.500 --> 19:40.500
TAPED UNDERNEATH
THE TABLE FOR YOU.

19:44.000 --> 19:46.467
HEY, WHERE'D
YOU GET THIS?

19:46.467 --> 19:49.400
TRADED MY 3000
FOR TWO 1500s.

19:49.400 --> 19:50.367
COOL!

19:52.200 --> 19:54.600
DAD, I KNOW YOU SAID
YOU HAD A ROUGH DAY,

19:54.600 --> 19:56.967
AND THAT YOU ONLY GET
TO BE A KID ONCE,

19:56.967 --> 19:59.767
BUT I THOUGHT IT'D BE OK
IF YOU CAME BACK TO VISIT.

20:03.900 --> 20:06.667
VISITING HOURS ARE
OUTSIDE IN THE YARD.

20:08.800 --> 20:10.600
[ALL SHOUT]

20:10.600 --> 20:12.500
NO SHOOTING
WATER GUNS

20:12.500 --> 20:13.834
IN THE HOUSE!

20:13.834 --> 20:15.200
MAYBE YOU WOULDN'T
FEEL THAT WAY

20:15.200 --> 20:18.300
IF YOU CHECKED UNDER
YOUR SIDE OF THE TABLE.

20:21.767 --> 20:23.100
THERE'S NOTHING THERE.

20:23.100 --> 20:24.900
WHAT DO YOU THINK,
I'M MADE OF MONEY?

20:24.900 --> 20:26.600
[ALL SHOUTING]

20:30.467 --> 20:31.767
DON'T HIT MY HAIR!

20:31.767 --> 20:33.367
Morgan: HIT HIS HAIR!

20:33.367 --> 20:34.133
YAAH! YAAH!

20:34.133 --> 20:36.667
I DON'T EVEN
HAVE A GUN!

20:36.667 --> 20:38.100
TRADE THE STUPID WATCH!

20:38.100 --> 20:39.767
[SHOUTING CONTINUES]

20:46.000 --> 20:48.100
COOKIES, MORGAN?

20:48.100 --> 20:50.200
SURE, I'D LOVE SOME.

21:03.367 --> 21:06.033
9-1-1.

21:07.200 --> 21:08.567
HELLO?

21:08.567 --> 21:12.300
YES. I'M STUCK HERE,
AND I CAN'T GET DOWN.

21:12.300 --> 21:15.300
MY PARENTS ARE
OUTSIDE FIGHTING.

21:15.300 --> 21:16.400
LISTEN.

21:19.000 --> 21:21.700
YOU'RE DROWNING
MY <i>FLORIBUNDAS! </i>

21:21.700 --> 21:24.600
THEY JUST SHOT
THE NEIGHBOR!

21:28.100 --> 21:30.767
HOLD ON. LET ME ASK.

21:30.767 --> 21:34.033
MOMMY!
WHAT'S OUR ADDRESS?
